14 Section 1148.16. The summons to be issued in an action for
15 forcible entry and detainer, commonly known as an eviction, shall be
16 in a form developed in plain and understandable language by the
17 Oklahoma Bar Association. The Administrative Office of the Courts
18 shall provide public access to the affidavit by providing a link to
19 the form on the Oklahoma State Courts Network (OSCN) website. The
20 summons shall be delivered no less than three (3) seven (7) days
21 before the scheduled time and date of the court hearing; provided,
22 however, a summons for an action pursuant to subsection C or D of
23 Section 132 of Title 41 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall be delivered
24 no less than three (3) days before the date of trial. This
